<div id="new-keyword-registration">
<section id="section-2.13">
        <h3 id="name-new-keyword-registration"><a href="#section-2.13">2.13.&nbsp;&nbsp;$new keyword registration</a></h3>
<span class="break"></span><dl class="dlCompact dlParallel" id="section-2.13-1">
          <dt id="section-2.13-1.1">IMAP/JMAP keyword name:</dt>
          <dd id="section-2.13-1.2">
            <code>$new</code><a href="#section-2.13-1.2" class="pilcrow">¶</a>
</dd>
          <dd class="break"></dd>
<dt id="section-2.13-1.3">Purpose:</dt>
          <dd id="section-2.13-1.4"> Indicate to the client that a message should be made more prominent to the user due to a recent action.<a href="#section-2.13-1.4" class="pilcrow">¶</a>
</dd>
          <dd class="break"></dd>
<dt id="section-2.13-1.5">Private or Shared on a server:</dt>
          <dd id="section-2.13-1.6"> SHARED<a href="#section-2.13-1.6" class="pilcrow">¶</a>
</dd>
          <dd class="break"></dd>
<dt id="section-2.13-1.7">Is it an advisory keyword or may it cause an automatic action:</dt>
          <dd id="section-2.13-1.8"> This keyword is advisory. Clients may show the status of the message.<a href="#section-2.13-1.8" class="pilcrow">¶</a>
</dd>
          <dd class="break"></dd>
<dt id="section-2.13-1.9">When/by whom the keyword is set/cleared:</dt>
          <dd id="section-2.13-1.10"> This keyword is set by an IMAP or JMAP server on messages after awakening them from snooze. Clients should clear the keyword when the message is opened.<a href="#section-2.13-1.10" class="pilcrow">¶</a>
</dd>
          <dd class="break"></dd>
